# Project Conventions

**Follow existing project conventions exactly.** Before writing new code, read nearby files that solve a similar problem and mirror how they do it.

Stack: **React 19**, **TypeScript** (strict), **TanStack Start/Router**, **TanStack React Query**, **Tailwind CSS v4**, **shadcn/ui** (Radix), **lucide-react**, **uPlot** for charts.

## Layout

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| Routes | `src/routes/` — TanStack file-based routing (`routeTree.gen.ts` is generated) |
| UI primitives | `src/components/ui/` — shadcn components; compound widgets in subfolders (`collapsible/`, `native-select/`) |
| App components | `src/components/` — grouped by domain, then role (see **File organization**) |
| API client | `src/lib/api/client.ts` + domain modules (`servers.ts`, `admin/`, etc.) |
| Query options | `src/lib/api/*.queries.ts` — React Query `queryOptions` factories |
| Auth | `src/lib/auth/` — context, session helpers, validation |
| Metrics / charts | `src/lib/metrics/` — range, series, chart config, uPlot theme |
| Utilities | `src/lib/` |
| Hooks | `src/hooks/` — domain subfolders (`chat/`, `metrics/`, `timeseries/`) |
| Global styles / theme | `src/styles.css` |
| Path alias | `@/*` → `src/*` |

## File organization

**Group by domain folder, then role — not flat prefix-heavy filenames.**

- Put related files in a subfolder and drop the redundant prefix from each filename.
  - `admin/settings/access-section.tsx`, not `admin/admin-settings-access-section.tsx`
  - `chat/widget/widget.tsx`, not `chat/tracker-chat-widget.tsx`
- Split large domains by role when it helps navigation:
  - `components/admin/settings/`, `admin/servers/`
  - `components/chat/widget/`, `chat/panel/`, `chat/turns/`, `chat/lib/`
  - `components/dashboard/cards/`, `controls/`, `server/` (+ existing `charts/`, `grids/`, `stats/`)
- Match existing subfolder patterns before inventing new ones. Read the sibling tree first.
- **No barrel re-exports** — do not add `index.ts` / `index.tsx` files that only `export { … } from "./…"`.
  - Import the source file directly: `@/components/ui/collapsible/root`, not `@/components/ui/collapsible`
  - Exception: TanStack Router route `index.tsx` files and modules that define real code (e.g. `lib/auth/index.ts` with `login`/`logout` implementations).
- Prefer relative imports within the same feature folder; use `@/` when crossing domains.

```tsx
// bad — barrel re-export
export { NativeSelect } from "./select";

// bad — flat prefixed siblings
components/admin/admin-settings-metrics-section.tsx
components/admin/admin-settings-dns-section.tsx

// good — grouped, short names, direct imports
import { NativeSelect } from "@/components/ui/native-select/select";
import { MetricsSettingsSection } from "@/components/admin/settings/metrics-section";
```

## Integration points

- **New pages** — add a route file under `src/routes/`; wire into `SiteHeader` nav if needed.
- **API calls** — use `apiFetch` from `@/lib/api/client`; default `credentials: "include"` for cookie auth. Use `queryOptions` + `useQuery`/`useMutation` — don't scatter raw `fetch`.
- **Metrics charts** — use existing chart helpers (`build-chart-config`, `metric-timeseries`, `uplot-theme`); align time windows with `MetricTimeRange` / `MetricTimeWindow`.
- **UI primitives** — match existing `src/components/ui/` patterns (CVA variants, `cn()`, Radix primitives, `Slot`).
- **Styling** — Tailwind utilities merged with `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`. Use theme tokens from `styles.css` (`bg-monitor-gray-100`, `text-warning`, `text-success`, `text-error`, shadcn semantic tokens) — not raw `neutral-*` scales or one-off hex. See `design-system.mdc`.
- **Inline `style`** — avoid for colors, spacing, and typography that belong in Tailwind or theme tokens. Use `style` only when the value is computed at runtime: chart dimensions, tooltip positioning.
- **Icons** — `lucide-react`, consistent sizing with sibling components.
- **Destructive actions** — confirm in a `Dialog` with plain-English summary; toast on successful save (`sonner`).
- **Secrets** — never store passwords or session secrets in client code. Auth is cookie-based only.

## Component design

**Model variation with types, not branching.** Use discriminated unions, CVA variant props, composition, or separate components — not string flags with `switch` chains.

- **Server status / metrics** — dedicated chart cards and dashboard components under `src/components/dashboard/` and `src/components/metrics/`.
- **Shared logic belongs up the tree** — extract a hook or shared component when multiple call sites need it.
- **Only where it earns its keep** — one variant with no second implementation stays concrete.

## Surrounding context

**Read the subsystem before you write code.**

- Trace an existing page end-to-end (route → components → query options → API client) before adding a sibling.
- Check `__root.tsx` / `SiteHeader` for layout and nav before changing page structure.
- No loose workarounds — don't bypass `apiFetch`, shadcn patterns, or the `@/` alias with one-off hacks.
